Reasoning: The paper deals with random coding exponents in channel coding and lossy source coding, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the extension of channel exponents to arbitrary D, which corresponds to erasure decoding and list decoding, topics related to coding theory (cs.SI). The paper also involves the derivation of exact random coding exponent, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical analysis and proofs, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
